The Chief Judge of the Federal High Court of Nigeria, Honorable Justice John Tsoho, has announced that the court will commence its annual vacation for the year 2022 on July 25.This, he said, was pursuant to the provisions of Order 46, Rule 4 (b) of the Federal High Court (Civil Procedures) Rules, 2019 (as amended). The vacation will commence on Monday, the 25th day of July 2022 from Friday, the 16th day of September 2022. Catherine Oby Christopher, Ph.D. Assistant Director Information, Federal High Court said in a statement on Wednesday that the vacation “is in order for Honourable Judges to enjoy their well-deserved rest and to prepare for the challenges of the new legal year. “The Court shall resume in all Judicial Divisions on Monday, the 19th of September, 2022.“During the vacation, only the Core Judicial Divisions (Abuja, Lagos and Port-Harcourt) will as usual remain functional for the litigating public to approach Division nearest to them. “It is crucial to stress that during the vacation, only cases of extreme urgencies, such as the arrest of ship(s) and fundamental rights enforcement are to be ordinarily entertained” Dr Oby Christopher stated. The Vacation Judges are: Abuja Division, Justice Ahmed Mohammed, Justice Emmanuel Nwite and Justice Nkeonye Maha. Lagos Division has:Justice D. E. Osiagor,Justice I.N. Oweibo, Justice A. Aluko andJustice T.G. Ringim.PortHarcourt Division has Justice P. M. Ayua, Justice A. T. Mohammed andJustice S.I. Mark.Meanwhile, the Chief Judge of the Federal High Court, Justice Tsoho, has wished his fellow Lordships a wonderful vacation in advance.